        <h3>WordPress Security</h3>
        <p>
            One of the major downsides of WordPress is how 3rd party code get's constantly and casually inserted into your website. Don't get me wrong most plugins are safe but their is a security risk you take especially when you install 3rd party plugins into your WordPress website. Often times you'll see headlines bounding around that theirs a new security flaw in a certain plugins that just recks havoc on a website. 
            
            A lot of these "too many chefs in the kitchen" some very obvious wholes start to become apparent with WordPress. The most glaring problem is the amount of 3rd party code you put into your website. WordPress users regularly have to stay on top of their updates due to malicious attacks from hackers who use 3rd party plugins to inject code into website.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

